Greetings to Macedonian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, today sent a message of greetings to Boris Trajkovski, President of Macedonia, on the occasion of its National Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message sent warm salutation to the President and people of Macedonia on this occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message sincerely wished the President success in his responsible work for the progress and prosperity of the country, expressing the belief that the cooperative relations between the two countries would steadily grow stronger.

Cambodian PM on Cambodia-DPRK friendly  relations 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- The friendly ties between Cambodia and Korea are based on the intimate relations between King Norodom Sihanouk and President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Hun Sen, Prime Minister of the Royal Government of Cambodia, said this when meeting with DPRK Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun and his party who paid a courtesy call on him on July 31. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He noted that he was well aware of the invariable support and encouragement sent by the DPRK to the just cause of the Cambodian people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK is more confidently advancing under the wise guidance of the great Kim Jong Il, raising its international position, he added.

Sports competition for "Jonsung Cup" held 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- Sports competition for "Jonsung Cup" was held in Pyongyang and local areas from July 6 to 29. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This is an annual event to mark the anniversary of the victory of the Korean people in the great Fatherland Liberation War (July 27). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Involved in the competition were ten maritime sports events including swimming, water skiing and yachting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Players of the Sobaeksu Sports Group and the sports groups of the Ministry of Fisheries and the Ministry of Land and Marine Transport gave a good account of themselves in the competition.

"Week of no smoking campaign" opens 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- A "week of no smoking campaign" opened with due ceremony in Pyongyang on August 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the opening ceremony were minister of public health Kim Su Hak, officials concerned, medical workers  and youth and students in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   George Fernando, advisor of the Mission for the Emergency and Humanitarian Action of the World Health Organization here, David Morton, resident coordinator of the United Nations and resident representative of the UNDP, and Kzahirul Karim, acting representative of the United Nations Children's Fund, were also present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "no smoking torch" was lighted to inaugurate the week. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Minister of Public Health Kim Su Hak in his opening address referred to the importance of the southeast Asian torch of the no smoking campaign.  The campaign carries weighty significance in encouraging the countries of the region to enhance their policy-making and leading role in the control over smoking  and mobilize many people in the campaign, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK reiterates its pledge to conduct more brisk and intensive activities to make the 21st century a century free from smoking and more positively cooperate in the implementation of the world no smoking policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Advisor George Fernando extended appreciation to the efforts of the DPRK government for protecting people from the habit of smoking and expressed the expectation that the DPRK would actively participate in the no smoking campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Then, they appreciated a performance given by a sanitary propaganda team before seeing photos on the harmful effect of smoking. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "week of no smoking campaign" will also open in Nampho, Phyongsong, Sariwon and other parts of the country.

U.S. government apology urged 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- The people's movement for revising the shackling "ROK-U.S. Status of Forces Agreement" which groups more than 100 civic organizations including the Citizens' Federation for Economic Justice and the Citizens' Solidarity for Democratic Society of South Korea held a rally in Seoul on July 29 with attendance of at least 300 students and citizens at which they demanded the U.S. government apologize for U.S. forces' dumping of poisonous substance in the River Han, the Seoul-based "Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation" reported. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As the provisions of the "agreement" are unilaterally in favour of the U.S. forces side, such crime of the U.S. forces as dumping of poisonous substance was committed, the organization claimed, pushing for the revision of all the shackling provisions of the "agreement".

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's work commemorated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il's historic work on modeling the whole society on the Juche idea by radically improving and strengthening the party work published on August 2, 1974 serves as a precious guideline to be held fast to by all party organizations in the ongoing dynamic drive to build a powerful country, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The ideas and theories laid down in the work clearly proved valid and vital in practice over the last 26 years, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A great vitality of the work lies in that the Worker's Party of Korea has developed to be a revolutionary party of Juche type that fully embodies the idea and intention of General Secretary Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Elucidated in the work are theoretical and practical problems which should be settled to strengthen and develop the party into a party of the leader including the issue of training all the officials and party members into elite revolutionaries boundlessly faithful to Kim Il Sung and conducting the party building and activities based on his ideas, theories and methods, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The WPK took on fresh new looks as a result of the successful embodiment of these ideas and theories. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   All the activities of the WPK are organized and conducted exactly as President Kim Il Sung intended and did in his lifetime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The validity and vitality of this work also lie in that the political and ideological unity and cohesion of the WPK have grown stronger than ever before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il in his work set forth specific tasks to ensure the purity of the party ranks and strengthen and develop the WPK into an invincible, united and revolutionary one and ways for their fulfillment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "arduous march" and forced march represented a proud course which demonstrated the unbreakable unity and cohesion of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The validity and vitality of the work has been also proved by the fact that the anti-Japanese guerrilla style of work has been fully introduced to the whole party to bring in a fresh turn in the method of party work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The article calls for exerting great efforts on firmly building up the ranks of the party and revolution and increasing its militancy under the uplifted banner of modeling the whole party on the Juche idea.

Thorough implementation of calls of C. C. of WPK urged 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- Papers here today editorially call on all the people to make a general advance in hearty response to the calls of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea published with the approach of its 55th anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The basic spirit of the calls lies in that the whole party and army and all the people should make a general charge to greet the 55th anniversary of the WPK as a great festival of victors and thus pave a new wide avenue for building a powerful nation, says Rodong Sinmun, the organ of the Central Committee of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   To carry through the calls represents a sacred struggle to fully demonstrate the might of single-hearted unity of the WPK, the army and people rallied close around the great Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   55 years of the WPK have clearly proved that if all the people are single-heartedly united around the party and leader in thought and purpose, morality and sense of obligation, they can beat any formidable enemy and there is nothing impossible for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   To thoroughly implement the calls is a worthwhile drive to fully demonstrate the indomitable stamina and heroic spirit of the Korean people who are making uninterrupted innovations and advance to achieve final victory despite whatever difficulties. It is the most honorable task before the party members and other working people to creditably discharge their mission and duty in this general advance as soldiers and disciples of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The whole party and army and all the people should devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution headed by Kim Jong Il, deeply grasp the greatness of his unique army-first politics and hold fast to the army-first revolutionary line as an invariable strategic line of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Victory is in store for us as long as there are his wise leadership and the correct line and policies of the experienced and seasoned WPK, the paper stresses, calling for more dynamically accelerating the general advance for building a powerful nation in hearty response to the calls of the WPK Central Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Minju Joson, the organ of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the cabinet of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, in an editorial calls on all the party members, working people and servicemen of the people's army to greet the 55th anniversary of the WPK as a great festival of victors true to the calls and thus demonstrate once again the heroic spirit of Korea of Juche, Kim Il Sung's nation.

Over 150 cases of aerial espionage recorded in July 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 2 (KCNA) -- The U.S. aggressors committed over 150 cases of aerial espionage against the DPRK in July, according to military sources. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Strategic and tactical reconnaissance planes including "U-2," "RC-135," "E-3" and "RF-4c" were involved in various espionage missions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   "U-2" high-altitude strategic reconnaissance plane made at least 40 espionage flights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On July 31 alone, this plane spied on strategic objects of the North Korea, flying over the areas along the military demarcation line.
